"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-summer-mcintosh-first-gold-medal-swimming-paris\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Check out Sports Illustrated\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Daily Rings, our daily Olympics podcast from Mitch Goldich and Dan Gartland.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 109, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 78, \"end\": 83, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Mitch\", \"score\": 0.9999998010489632, \"rank\": 1.952465216641987e-07, \"text\": \"Mitch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Mitch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Mitch\"}, {\"begin\": 100, \"end\": 108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\", \"score\": 0.9999999801552806, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gartland\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Subscribe wherever you get your podcasts (Apple,Spotify) and find clips onSI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s YouTube page.\", \"from\": 110, \"to\": 204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 152, \"end\": 157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 0.9999999998822204, \"rank\": 8.946861041094487e-11, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}, {\"begin\": 158, \"end\": 165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Spotify\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NANTERRE, France \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 Summer McIntosh is not yet 18, but when she arrived at the Paris La D\\u00c3\\u00a9fense Arena pool for the 400-meter individual medley final Monday evening, she was not just expected to win a gold medal.\", \"from\": 206, \"to\": 419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 206, \"end\": 214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\", \"score\": 0.999999944000139, \"rank\": 5.3521478807018674e-08, \"text\": \"NANTERRE\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\"}, {\"begin\": 227, \"end\": 242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It wasassumedshe would win the gold medal.\", \"from\": 420, \"to\": 462, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh had already won silver in the 400 free, and while every Olympic silver is an amazing achievement, silver in a race when Katie Ledecky wins bronze feels even more impressive.\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 463, \"end\": 471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7471716597818746e-14, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 592, \"end\": 605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But McIntosh merely competes in the 400 free.\", \"from\": 646, \"to\": 691, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 650, \"end\": 658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7471716597818746e-14, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 400 IM, she owns.\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 713, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is where we would normally talk about the extraordinary pressure a 17-year-old in that situation must feel, but it would be a bit disingenuous.\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 863, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At last year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s world championships, McIntosh won the 400 IM by more than four seconds.Since then, she has gotten faster: She set the world record of 4:24.38 at the Canadian Olympic Trials.\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 1054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 902, \"end\": 910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7471716597818746e-14, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 1030, \"end\": 1038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9062170091598987, \"rank\": 0.06430443671466751, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 1039, \"end\": 1053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"score\": 0.8581582794952675, \"rank\": 0.038961038961052005, \"text\": \"Olympic Trials\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pressure was not going to cost McIntosh gold.\", \"from\": 1056, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1087, \"end\": 1095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7471716597818746e-14, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A stomach virus, maybe.\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But not pressure.\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1143, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh knew it, too, not because she is arrogant, but because she knows what she is capable of.\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1145, \"end\": 1153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7471716597818746e-14, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She said afterward that as she made the turn in the breaststroke, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI kind of looked around to make sure I was in a comfortable lead.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d The race was not even half over.\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI definitely knew that I had the gold medal going into that last 100 meters,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d McIntosh said.\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1513, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1499, \"end\": 1507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7471716597818746e-14, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was her first gold medal, and even that sounds absurd, inasmuch as it implies she will win more.\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1614, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 shewillwin more.\", \"from\": 1615, \"to\": 1639, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh won the 200 butterfly at the last two world championships; that race is Wednesday.\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1731, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1640, \"end\": 1648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7471716597818746e-14, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cObviously, I am super happy with the result, but now I am all about the [200] fly on Day Five,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d McIntosh said.\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1834, \"end\": 1842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7471716597818746e-14, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The question, with an athlete who is this good this young, is whether she appreciates how special it is to win gold.\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1966, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s official answer: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cOh, yeah, for sure.\", \"from\": 1967, \"to\": 2019, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I mean, definitely pretty surreal.\", \"from\": 2020, \"to\": 2054, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was very happy to get the job done tonight.\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2100, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That was a goal of mine, to be able to stand on top of the podium and get the gold medal.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  The honest answer is that she probably can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t appreciate this.\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2258, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not fully.\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2269, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She can understand it intellectually, and she can try to savor it.\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2336, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But McIntosh is still just 17.\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2341, \"end\": 2349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7471716597818746e-14, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Appreciation can only come later, after life experience and some tougher moments in the pool allow her to put this into proper emotional context.\", \"from\": 2368, \"to\": 2513, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is fair to say Michael Phelps appreciates thesix gold medals he won in Athensa lot more now than he did in 2004.\", \"from\": 2514, \"to\": 2629, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2532, \"end\": 2546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5175699405972307e-48, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Katie Ledecky was 15 when she won her first gold medal.\", \"from\": 2630, \"to\": 2685, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2630, \"end\": 2643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Who can make sense of something like that at 15?\", \"from\": 2686, \"to\": 2734, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Full appreciation is the gift that McIntosh unknowingly wrapped for herself Monday night, to be opened at a much later date.\", \"from\": 2736, \"to\": 2860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2771, \"end\": 2779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7471716597818746e-14, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For now, she at least seems to have avoided the traps that can come with others\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 assumption of greatness.\", \"from\": 2861, \"to\": 2968, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Somebody asked if she felt any relief at winning gold.\", \"from\": 2970, \"to\": 3024, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a reasonable question, considering her dominance.\", \"from\": 3025, \"to\": 3081, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Butreliefat winning gold at 17 years old?\", \"from\": 3082, \"to\": 3123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAbsolutely not,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d McIntosh said.\", \"from\": 3125, \"to\": 3161, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3147, \"end\": 3155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7471716597818746e-14, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThere is definitely a lot of anticipation going into a race, but I would not say necessarily nerves, and there is no relief.\", \"from\": 3162, \"to\": 3289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am just trying to soak up every single moment.\", \"from\": 3290, \"to\": 3338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 I still feel like I am my 10-year-old self, and I am just trying to solidify all those dreams I had growing up as a kid.\", \"from\": 3339, \"to\": 3463, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I plan on being in the sport for as long as I can do it.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 3464, \"to\": 3551, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Michael Rosenberg is a senior writer for Sports Illustrated, covering any and all sports.\", \"from\": 3552, \"to\": 3705, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3616, \"end\": 3633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Rosenberg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.619208256351329e-16, \"text\": \"Michael Rosenberg\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Rosenberg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Rosenberg\"}, {\"begin\": 3657, \"end\": 3675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7786634041593366e-22, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He writes columns, profiles and investigative stories and has covered almost every major sporting event.\", \"from\": 3706, \"to\": 3810, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He joined SI in 2012 after working at the Detroit Free Press for 13 years, eight of them as a columnist.\", \"from\": 3811, \"to\": 3915, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3853, \"end\": 3871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Detroit_Free_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Detroit Free Press\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Detroit_Free_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Detroit_Free_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rosenberg is the author of \\\"War As They Knew It: Woody Hayes, Bo Schembechler and America in a Time of Unrest.\\\"\", \"from\": 3916, \"to\": 4027, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3916, \"end\": 3925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julius_and_Ethel_Rosenberg\", \"score\": 0.9862514680845195, \"rank\": 0.01394018457864383, \"text\": \"Rosenberg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julius_and_Ethel_Rosenberg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julius_and_Ethel_Rosenberg\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Several of his stories also have been published in collections of the year's best sportswriting.\", \"from\": 4028, \"to\": 4124, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He is married with three children.\", \"from\": 4125, \"to\": 4159, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC.\", \"from\": 4161, \"to\": 4238, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 4239, \"to\": 4261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only.\", \"from\": 4262, \"to\": 4338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands.\", \"from\": 4339, \"to\": 4533, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4466, \"end\": 4484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7786634041593366e-22, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit.\", \"from\": 4534, \"to\": 4622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\", \"from\": 4623, \"to\": 4755, \"entities\": []}]}"